Girardinia diversifolia

    Authority
      Family
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 38133

   Notes
   Herbaceous plant with stems often woody at base, straight, branched or
   not, 5-angled, 25-200 cm tall. Stems and petioles spreading pubescent
   and armed with stinging and stigose hairs. USE: Produces up to 65 cm
   long fibres. In Nepal, fibres are extracted and used for knitted or
   woven textiles and paper. Leaves and flowers are edible and the plant
   has medicinal properties. GROWING PERIOD: Annual or perennial. COMMON
   NAMES: Giant nettle. FURTHER INF: In Nepal, it can be found along
   forest margins and streams, in light forest, shady moist places,
   disturbed places and near villages at elevations between 100-3000 m.
   Also found in Bhutan, India, Indonesia, Korea, Malaysia, Nepal, Sikkim,
   Sri Lanka and Africa (including Madagascar)

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
